===== Inserting new elements in a BST

.For inserting an element, in a BST, we have two scenarios:
1.  If the tree is empty (root element is null), we add the newly created node as root, and that's it!
2.  If the root is not null. Start from it and compare the node‚Äôs value against the new element. If the node has higher than a new item, we move to the right child, otherwise to the left. We check each node recursively until we find an empty spot where we can put the new element and keep the rule `right < parent < left`.
3.  If we insert the same value multiple times, we don‚Äôt want duplicates. So, we can keep track of multiples using a duplicity counter.

